<div id="review_79675188" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/79675188" />
    <a title="Lauren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6078-lauren"><img alt="Lauren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1197260498p2/6078.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/79675188?book_show_action=true">Dec 02, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lauren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lauren" href="/user/show/6078-lauren">Lauren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79675188" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11249247556825292732">What a beautiful, transporting book. I lost track of subway stops today which is always the mark of an excellent book.<br/><br/>Whenever a book is set in the South, I get anxious about the depiction of Southerners and I was a bit leery at first. Nevertheless, Greene is a remarkable storyteller and thanks to her terrific narration, her characters come to life in a rich, yet nuanced manner. I felt she had just the right touch, revealing in pieces and always leaving you aching for more. Like another reviewer</span>
  <span id="freeText11249247556825292732" style="display:none">What a beautiful, transporting book. I lost track of subway stops today which is always the mark of an excellent book.<br /><br />Whenever a book is set in the South, I get anxious about the depiction of Southerners and I was a bit leery at first. Nevertheless, Greene is a remarkable storyteller and thanks to her terrific narration, her characters come to life in a rich, yet nuanced manner. I felt she had just the right touch, revealing in pieces and always leaving you aching for more. Like another reviewer, I had to remember to breathe as I raced toward the end of the novel. I also had to hold in my tears. I hope many people find this book and enjoy it as much as I did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11249247556825292732" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
