  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1113065764" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1113065764" />
    <a title="Donna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13244359-donna"><img alt="Donna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396758075p2/13244359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1113065764?book_show_action=true">Nov 22, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna" href="/user/show/13244359-donna">Donna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1113065764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3384362653275370602">I don&apos;t even know where to start. There are so many things rolling around in my head and my heart.<br/><br/>I did the audio and it was great. The readers were amazing. They brought the characters to life that would have made the author swell with pride. <br/><br/>This was told from several different points of view. I&apos;m usually not a fan of that format, but it seemed to work in this book.<br/><br/>The author breathed real life into her characters through such a strong descriptive style. Her descriptions were focused, vivid an</span>
  <span id="freeText3384362653275370602" style="display:none">I don't even know where to start. There are so many things rolling around in my head and my heart.<br /><br />I did the audio and it was great. The readers were amazing. They brought the characters to life that would have made the author swell with pride. <br /><br />This was told from several different points of view. I'm usually not a fan of that format, but it seemed to work in this book.<br /><br />The author breathed real life into her characters through such a strong descriptive style. Her descriptions were focused, vivid and specific, both physically and emotionally. I felt they were right there and I had a front row seat. As an avid reader and listener, I really like that. I will read more by this author. She has the type of writing talent that I typically rave about. The story was also well thought out and it, too, felt real. Sometimes when plots are extremely cultural, it can be heavy handed. I didn't get that feel, but the hillbilly/redneck mentality was quite jarring.<br /><br />So I am feeling conflicted here. I'm not sure I liked the story. Actually it wasn't even the story itself. It was the uneasiness I felt because of the fictional reality of the fictional characters. That is what I didn't like. It felt very personal, raw and revealing. It had me feeling like I was on high alert. I sometimes felt like I wanted to sound the warning bell and other times I wanted to be invisible. <br /><br />So how do I even rate that? If I could remove my gut reaction to this story, it would be 4 or 5 stars. Also, it made me feel something (even though it was not in a good way). All these things I tend to rate highly. But I just can't do it. I can only do 3 stars and that is for the writing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3384362653275370602" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

